overview_summary: All three profiled neighbors are local landowners in rural Dane County with no documented public stance on the proposed development. None have publicly supported or opposed clean energy projects in the area, and their community influence appears limited to their landholdings. One neighbor (Caldwell) holds multiple parcels and thus has somewhat greater presence, but overall influence remains low. All are currently categorized as neutral/unknown in stance.

neighbors.name: Patricia E. Johnson
neighbors.claims: Patricia E. Johnson is listed as the owner of an agricultural parcel in rural Dane County, Wisconsin ([dailyreporter.com](https://dailyreporter.com/2021/11/18/regulators-dismiss-towns-attempt-to-block-650m-solar-farm-in-dane-county/#:~:text=In%20filings%20before%20the%20PSC,the%20project%20to%20the%20PSC)). She has not taken a prominent public role in local development debates; for example, she was not among residents who formally challenged a recent large-scale solar project in the county ([dailyreporter.com](https://dailyreporter.com/2021/11/18/regulators-dismiss-towns-attempt-to-block-650m-solar-farm-in-dane-county/#:~:text=In%20filings%20before%20the%20PSC,the%20project%20to%20the%20PSC)). No public statements or letters from Johnson about development or land use were found in available records, suggesting her stance remains private or undefined ([www.wpr.org](https://www.wpr.org/agriculture/residents-share-mixed-feelings-over-states-largest-proposed-renewable-energy-plant-dane-county#:~:text=Multiple%20residents%20expressed%20concerns%20about,of%20public%20hearing%20Thursday%20night)).

approach_recommendations.engage: Reach out personally with assurances that her rural lifestyle and farmland value will be respected. Emphasize how project plans include land preservation measures and minimal visual impact, addressing any concerns about maintaining the area’s rural character.

neighbors.name: Sharon E. Haug
neighbors.claims: Sharon E. Haug owns a parcel of land in Dane County that is zoned for agricultural use, consistent with the area’s farmland preservation policies ([lwrd.danecounty.gov](https://lwrd.danecounty.gov/What-We-Do/agriculture/Conservation-Initiatives/Farmland-Preservation-Program#:~:text=Dane%20County%E2%80%99s%20Farmland%20Preservation%20Plan,DATCP%29%20to%20determine%20eligibility)). She has no record of publicly voicing support or opposition to local development or renewable energy projects ([www.wpr.org](https://www.wpr.org/agriculture/residents-share-mixed-feelings-over-states-largest-proposed-renewable-energy-plant-dane-county#:~:text=Multiple%20residents%20expressed%20concerns%20about,of%20public%20hearing%20Thursday%20night)). Haug did not participate in recent formal objections to large projects in the community, indicating that her position on such developments has not been publicly asserted ([dailyreporter.com](https://dailyreporter.com/2021/11/18/regulators-dismiss-towns-attempt-to-block-650m-solar-farm-in-dane-county/#:~:text=In%20filings%20before%20the%20PSC,the%20project%20to%20the%20PSC)).

approach_recommendations.engage: Approach with a neighborly conversation emphasizing respect for local farmland and scenery. Highlight project aspects that protect farm operations and rural views, and offer to address any questions about how land and landscape will be managed.

neighbors.name: Rodney W. Caldwell
neighbors.claims: Rodney W. Caldwell is a prominent landowner in the area, with multiple agricultural parcels in Dane County registered under his name ([dailyreporter.com](https://dailyreporter.com/2021/11/18/regulators-dismiss-towns-attempt-to-block-650m-solar-farm-in-dane-county/#:~:text=Plans%20for%20the%20Koshkonong%20Solar,Electric%20will%20own%20the%20rest)). Despite his extensive landholdings, there is no indication that Caldwell has publicly taken a side on development or clean energy proposals; he has not been identified in any public hearings or legal actions regarding such projects ([dailyreporter.com](https://dailyreporter.com/2021/11/18/regulators-dismiss-towns-attempt-to-block-650m-solar-farm-in-dane-county/#:~:text=In%20filings%20before%20the%20PSC,the%20project%20to%20the%20PSC)). Like many in the community, his primary interest likely centers on preserving the use and value of his farmland, although he has not made formal statements on the matter ([znetwork.org](https://znetwork.org/znetarticle/the-small-towns-rejecting-solar-farms/#:~:text=%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20not%20anti,village%20board%20not%20to%20drop)).

approach_recommendations.engage: Engage Mr. Caldwell through one-on-one dialogue via a trusted local farming peer. Emphasize how the project can coexist with farming interests and uphold the rural character of the area, addressing any concerns he may have about land preservation or visual impact.
